            <tr>
                <td class="esd-structure" align="left">
                    <table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td class="esd-container-frame" width="600" valign="top" align="center">
                                    <table width="100%" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                                        <tbody>
                                            <tr>
                                                <td class="esd-block-text es-p30t es-p10b es-p20r es-p20l" align="center" bgcolor="#e6f2fb" esd-links-color="#3d85c6">
                                                    <p style="font-size: 22px;"><strong>Vitamin B requirements</strong></p>
                                                    <p style="text-align: left;">Vitamin B is a family of water soluble vitamins which essentially means they are dissolved in water & is carried through body tissue but are not stored in the body. Like Vitamin C, it acts as cofactor for various enzymes to carry out various bodily processes. Some of important functions of Vitamin B include</p>
                                                    <ol>
                                                        <li>
                                                            <p style="text-align: left;">Protein, fat & carbohydrate metabolism.</p>
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                            <p style="text-align: left;">DNA synthesis</p>
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                            <p style="text-align: left;">Supporting Nerve cell function</p>
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                            <p style="text-align: left;">Red blood cell production.</p>
                                                        </li>
                                                    </ol>
                                                    <p style="text-align: left;">Most of B vitamins like Vitamin B6 & B9 are synthesised in plants with exception of Vitamin B-12 which is made by bacteria in the gut of mammals. Some yeast & fungi create Vitamin B-12 but its bioavailability is low.</p>
                                                    <p style="text-align: left;"><br></p>
                                                    <p style="text-align: left;">We can meet our Vitamin B-12 requirement through consumption of&nbsp; fish, meat, poultry,shellfish, liver, eggs & dairy products. It is an essential cofactor required for our body to function effectively.</p>
                                                    <p style="text-align: left;"><br></p>
                                                    <p style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://thesushantkumar.com/2020/10/17/vitamin-b12-absorption/" style="color: #3d85c6;"><u>Vitamin B-12</u></a> is a cofactor for enzyme methionine synthase. This enzyme makes amino acid-methionine which is then used to make an important molecule S-adenosylmethionine (SAM). SAM & Vitamin B12 is important for a chemical process known as methylation. This is used for various processes which includes:</p>
                                                    <ol>
                                                        <li>
                                                            <p style="text-align: left;">Making DNA</p>
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                            <p style="text-align: left;">Switching genes on & off</p>
                                                        </li>
                                                        <li>
                                                            <p style="text-align: left;">Producing Neurotransmitters & proteins.</p>
                                                        </li>
                                                    </ol>
                                                    <p style="text-align: left;"><a href="https://thesushantkumar.com/product/online-fitness-coaching/" style="color: #3d85c6;"><u>Sign up</u></a> for our genetics based preventive health coaching solution to figure out if you need to restructure intake of these nutrients to achieve optimal health.</p>
                                                    <p style="text-align: left;"><br></p>
